","by 1292 no issue":"1292","about 1265":"about 1265","1318":"1318","1317":"1317","Halton, Runcorn, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Halton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Halton, Lancashire,England":"Halton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Halton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Halton, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gernet","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(2010: NA)","German: derivative of Middle High German <i>gern</i> ‘to desire’, a component of various ancient Germanic personal names such as <i>Gernhard</i>. Alternatively, a variant of   Gernot  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gernot","meanings":["(2010: NA)","German: from an ancient Germanic personal name composed of the elements <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>knōt-</i> ‘(to) swing’."]}]},{"name":"Benet","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Church Latin <i>benedictus</i> ‘blessed’. This was the name of the saint (  <i>c.</i>480– <i>c.</i>550 ) who composed the Benedictine rule of Christian monastic life that is still followed in essence by all Western orders. He was born near Spoleto in Umbria, central Italy. After studying in Rome, he went to live as a hermit at Subiaco, and later organized groups of followers and imitators into monastic cells. In  <i>c.</i>529  he moved to Monte Cassino, where he founded the great monastery that is still the centre of the Benedictine order. His rule is simple, restrained, and practical.  See also  Bennett ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":29,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Pa